--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages pwgen.

pwgen generates random, meaningless but pronounceable passwords. These passwords
contain either only lowercase letters, or upper and lower case, or upper case,
lower case and numeric digits. Upper case letters and numeric digits are placed
in a way that eases memorizing the password.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: pwgen
       pwgen_state: 'install'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: pwgen
       pwgen_state: 'remove'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  pwgen_state
    Specify predetermined 'pwgen_state' variable (string).

    Install: 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
    Remove : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'
    Default: 'install'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DEPENDENCIES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

PACKAGES
  pwgen: >= 2.06
    RedHat, CentOS, Gentoo

